[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hafodyrynys incident leaves man critical and two arrested

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man is in a critical condition in hospital after an incident in Caerphilly county, Gwent Police have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He received serious injuries, with emergency services called to Hafodyrynys, near Crumlin, at around 03:40 GMT on Tuesday.
Two men, aged 35 and 32, were arrested and are in police custody.
Officers are continuing to investigate and appealed for witnesses.
